CatDescriptText: Miss Mariam Hutton, IBM operator, Millvale and Mr. Julius Austin, painter, Wilkinsburg, were part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in the Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, September 9, 1961, pg. 5 with question: "Do you think that in the final analysis, the uncommitted darker nations will join the democratic (pro-Western) or Communistic bloc?  Why?" Miss Mariam Hutton's answer reads: "I don't know who they will join, but i hope they join us."  Mr. Julius Austin's answer reads: "I think it will be the democratic bloc, because it has more of our ways."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Mariam Hutton wearing short sleeved button down collared shirt, standing in front of sign inscribed "Measurements Same Day Service select...Brun...Shoes and ..."; Portrait of Julius Austin wearing dark polo shirt and checkered hat, standing with arms crossed in front of store window
